{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-sistent-component-js-content-file-path-src-collections-sistent-components-button-group-code-mdx","path":"/projects/sistent/components/button-group/code","result":{"data":{"mdx":{"body":"\nimport { ButtonGroup, Button, Box } from \"@sistent/sistent\";\n\nexport const buttons = [\n  <Button key=\"one\">One</Button>,\n  <Button key=\"two\">Two</Button>,\n  <Button key=\"three\">Three</Button>,\n];\n\nThe ButtonGroup component can be used to group related buttons together. It is a container for multiple buttons that can be used to group buttons together and apply styles to them. This component is useful when you have a group of buttons that need to be styled in a similar way.\n\n<a id=\"Basic Usage\">\n  <h2>Basic Usage</h2>\n</a>\n\nThe buttons can be grouped by wrapping them with the ButtonGroup component. They need to be immediate children.\n\n<div className=\"showcase\">\n  <div className=\"items\">\n    <ThemeWrapper>\n      <ButtonGroup variant=\"contained\" aria-label=\"Basic button group\">\n        {buttons}\n      </ButtonGroup>\n    </ThemeWrapper>\n  </div>\n  <CodeBlock name=\"basic-usage\" collapsible code={`<ButtonGroup variant=\"contained\" aria-label=\"Basic bgroup\">\n  <Button>One</Button>\n  <Button>Two</Button>\n  <Button>Three</Button>\n</ButtonGroup>`} />\n</div>\n\n<a id=\"Button Variant\">\n  <h2>Button Variant</h2>\n</a>\n\nThe ButtonGroup component supports three variants: Filled, Outlined, and Text.\n\n<div className=\"showcase\">\n  <div className=\"items\">\n    <ThemeWrapper>\n      <div style={{ display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', alignItems: 'center', gap: '8px' }}>\n        <ButtonGroup variant=\"contained\" aria-label=\"Basic button group\">\n            {buttons}\n        </ButtonGroup>\n        <ButtonGroup variant=\"outlined\" aria-label=\"Basic button group\">\n            {buttons}\n        </ButtonGroup>\n        <ButtonGroup variant=\"text\" aria-label=\"Basic button group\">\n            {buttons}\n        </ButtonGroup>\n      </div>\n    </ThemeWrapper>\n  </div>\n  <CodeBlock name=\"button-variant\" collapsible code={`<ButtonGroup\n    variant=\"contained\"\n    aria-label=\"Basic button group\"\n  >\n    <Button>One</Button>\n    <Button>Two</Button>\n    <Button>Three</Button>\n  </ButtonGroup>\n  <ButtonGroup variant=\"outlined\" aria-label=\"Basic bugroup\">\n    <Button>One</Button>\n    <Button>Two</Button>\n    <Button>Three</Button>\n  </ButtonGroup>\n  <ButtonGroup variant=\"text\" aria-label=\"Basic button group\">\n    <Button>One</Button>\n    <Button>Two</Button>\n    <Button>Three</Button>\n</ButtonGroup>`} />\n</div>\n\n<a id=\"Vertical Group\">\n  <h2>Vertical Group</h2>\n</a>\n\nThe ButtonGroup component can be used to create a vertical group of buttons by setting the vertical prop to true.\n\n<div className=\"showcase\">\n  <div className=\"items\">\n    <ThemeWrapper>\n      <div style={{ display: 'flex', justifyContent: 'center', gap: '8px' }}>\n          <ButtonGroup\n            orientation=\"vertical\"\n            variant=\"contained\"\n            aria-label=\"Basic button group\"\n          >\n            {buttons}\n          </ButtonGroup>\n          <ButtonGroup\n            orientation=\"vertical\"\n            variant=\"outlined\"\n            aria-label=\"Basic button group\"\n          >\n            {buttons}\n          </ButtonGroup>\n          <ButtonGroup\n            orientation=\"vertical\"\n            variant=\"text\"\n            aria-label=\"Basic button group\"\n          >\n            {buttons}\n          </ButtonGroup>\n      </div>\n    </ThemeWrapper>\n  </div>\n  <CodeBlock name=\"vertical-group\" collapsible code={`<ButtonGroup\n    orientation=\"vertical\"\n    variant=\"contained\"\n    aria-label=\"Basic button group\"\n  >\n    <Button>One</Button>\n    <Button>Two</Button>\n    <Button>Three</Button>\n  </ButtonGroup>\n  <ButtonGroup\n    orientation=\"vertical\"\n    variant=\"outlined\"\n    aria-label=\"Basic button group\"\n  >\n    <Button>One</Button>\n    <Button>Two</Button>\n    <Button>Three</Button>\n  </ButtonGroup>\n  <ButtonGroup\n    orientation=\"vertical\"\n    variant=\"text\"\n    aria-label=\"Basic button group\"\n  >\n    <Button>One</Button>\n    <Button>Two</Button>\n    <Button>Three</Button>\n</ButtonGroup>`} />\n</div>\n\n<a id=\"Disable elevation\">\n  <h2>Disable elevation</h2>\n</a>\n\nThe ButtonGroup component can be used to create a group of buttons with no elevation by setting the disableElevation prop to true.\n\n<div className=\"showcase\">\n  <div className=\"items\">\n    <ThemeWrapper>\n      <ButtonGroup\n        disableElevation\n        variant=\"contained\"\n        aria-label=\"Basic button group\"\n      >\n        {buttons}\n      </ButtonGroup>\n    </ThemeWrapper>\n  </div>\n  <CodeBlock name=\"disable-elevation\" collapsible code={`<ButtonGroup\n  disableElevation\n  variant=\"contained\"\n  aria-label=\"Basic button group\"\n>\n  <Button>One</Button>\n  <Button>Two</Button>\n  <Button>Three</Button>\n</ButtonGroup>`} />\n</div>\n\n<a id=\"Sizes\">\n  <h2>Sizes</h2>\n</a>\n\nFor now, two different sizes of buttons exist: 56px height and 48px height.\n\n<div className=\"showcase\">\n  <div className=\"items\">\n    <ThemeWrapper>\n        <div style={{ display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', alignItems: 'center', gap: '8px' }}>\n          <ButtonGroup\n            size=\"small\"\n            variant=\"contained\"\n            aria-label=\"Basic button group\"\n          >\n            {buttons}\n          </ButtonGroup>\n          <ButtonGroup\n            size=\"medium\"\n            variant=\"contained\"\n            aria-label=\"Basic button group\"\n          >\n            {buttons}\n          </ButtonGroup>\n          <ButtonGroup\n            size=\"large\"\n            variant=\"contained\"\n            aria-label=\"Basic button group\"\n          >\n            {buttons}\n          </ButtonGroup>\n      </div>\n    </ThemeWrapper>\n  </div>\n  <CodeBlock name=\"sizes\" collapsible code={`<ButtonGroup\n    size=\"small\"\n    variant=\"contained\"\n    aria-label=\"Basic button group\"\n  >\n    <Button>One</Button>\n    <Button>Two</Button>\n    <Button>Three</Button>\n  </ButtonGroup>\n  <ButtonGroup\n    size=\"medium\"\n    variant=\"contained\"\n    aria-label=\"Basic button group\"\n  >\n    <Button>One</Button>\n    <Button>Two</Button>\n    <Button>Three</Button>\n  </ButtonGroup>\n  <ButtonGroup\n    size=\"large\"\n    variant=\"contained\"\n    aria-label=\"Basic button group\"\n  >\n    <Button>One</Button>\n    <Button>Two</Button>\n    <Button>Three</Button>\n</ButtonGroup>`} />\n</div>\n\n<a id=\"Full Width\">\n  <h2>Full Width</h2>\n</a>\n\nThe ButtonGroup component can be used to create a group of buttons that take up the full width of the container by setting the fullWidth prop to true.\n\n<div className=\"showcase\">\n  <div className=\"items\">\n    <ThemeWrapper>\n      <ButtonGroup\n        fullWidth\n        variant=\"contained\"\n        aria-label=\"Basic button group\"\n      >\n        {buttons}\n      </ButtonGroup>\n    </ThemeWrapper>\n  </div>\n  <CodeBlock name=\"full-width\" collapsible code={`<ButtonGroup\n  fullWidth\n  variant=\"contained\"\n  aria-label=\"Basic button group\"\n>\n  <Button>One</Button>\n  <Button>Two</Button>\n  <Button>Three</Button>\n</ButtonGroup>`} />\n</div>\n","frontmatter":{"title":"Button Group Code","description":"The ButtonGroup component can be used to group related buttons together. It is a container for multiple buttons that can be used to group buttons together and apply styles to them. This component is useful when you have a group of buttons that need to be styled in a similar way."}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/projects/sistent/components/button-group/code","componentName":"button-group","availablePages":["code","overview","guidance"],"frontmatter":{"title":"Button Group Code","component":"button-group","description":"The ButtonGroup component can be used to group related buttons together. It is a container for multiple buttons that can be used to group buttons together and apply styles to them. This component is useful when you have a group of buttons that need to be styled in a similar way."}}},"staticQueryHashes":["4152005505","934084603"],"slicesMap":{}}